Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Boil the @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{250%grams}, ~{3%mins}.

Once cooked, drain.

Meanwhile, add the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Fresh Pesto{32%grams}, @Peas{120%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} to
a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Stir together. Simmer, ~{1-2%mins}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the ravioli to the pesto sauce, stirring gently to combine.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{}.

Enjoy!